What you need to know:

David Osamba runs a firm through which he hires out transplanters, walking tractors and power reapers to smallholder farmers growing maize, rice and sugar cane in various counties in Western in a unique business model.The information technology scientist turned agribusiness entrepreneur runs Nyabon Enterprises, through which he owns several small farm machines that he hires out to rice, maize and cane farmers in Kisumu and Homa Bay counties.He registered his business and invested his savings in importing the small engine tractors for sale in Kenya.Â To hire a power tiller (walking tractor), a farmer pays Sh3,000 per day, and the manually driven machine can till up to 1.5 acres per day.